obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (1100)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 8
  title `Total number of seats in Legislative Assemblies and Assembly Constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1100&sectionno=7&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1[7. Total number of seats in the Legislative Assemblies and Assembly Constituencies.--(1) ^2[Subject to the provisions of ^3[sub-sections (1A), (1B) and (1C)], the total number of seats] in the`
  line `Legislative Assembly of each State specified in the Second Schedule, to be filled by persons chosen`
  line `by direct election from Assembly Constituencies, and the number of seats, if any, to be reserved for`
  line `the Scheduled Castes and for the Scheduled Tribes of the State, shall be as shown in that Schedule:`
  line
  line `Provided that for the period referred to in clause (2) of article 371A, the total number of seats allotted to the Legislative Assembly of the State of Nagaland shall be ^4[fifty-two], of which--`
  line
  line `(a) ^5[twelve seats] shall be allocated to the Tuensang district and shall be filled by persons`
  line `persons chosen by the members of the regional council, referred to in that article, from amongst`
  line `themselves in such manner as the Governor, after consulting that Council may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, specify, and`
  line
  line `(b) the remaining forty seats shall be filled by persons chosen by direct election from`
  line `assembly constituencies in the rest of the State.`
  line
  line `^6[(1A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the total number of seats in the`
  line `the Legislative Assembly of the State of Sikkim, to be constituted at any time after the`
  line `commencement of the Representation of the People (Amendment) Act, 1980 (8 of 1980), to be filled by persons chosen by direct election from assembly constituencies shall be thirty-two, of`
  line which--
  line
  line `(a) twelve seats shall be reserved for Sikkimese of Bhutia-Lepcha origin;`
  line
  line `(b) two seats shall be reserved for the Scheduled Castes of that State; and`
  line
  line `(c) one seat shall be reserved for the Sanghas referred to in section 25A.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this sub-section Bhutia includes Chumbipa, Dopthapa, Dukpa, Kagatey,`
  line `Sherpa, Tibetan, Tromopa and Yolmo.]`
  line
  line `^7[(1B) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), in the Legislative Assemblies of`
  line `the States of Arunachal Pradesh, Meghalaya, Mizoram and Nagaland, to be constituted at any`
  line `time after the commencement of the Representation of the People (Third Amendment) Act, 1987`
  line `(40 of 1987),--`
  line
  line `(a) ^8[fifty-nine seats] shall be reserved for the Scheduled Tribes in the Legislative Assembly`
  line `of the State of Arunachal Pradesh;`
  line
  line `(b) fifty-five seats shall be reserved for the Scheduled Tribes in the Legislative Assembly of`
  line `the State of Meghalaya;`
  line
  line `(c) thirty-nine seats shall be reserved for the Scheduled Tribes in the Legislative Assembly`
  line `of the State of Mizoram; and`
  line
  line `(d) fifty-nine seats shall be reserved for the Scheduled Tribes in the Legislative Assembly of`
  line `the State of Nagaland.]`
  line
  line `^9[(1C) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), twenty seats shall be reserved`
  line `for the Scheduled Tribes in the Legislative Assembly of the State of Tripura to be constituted at any`
  line `time after the commencement of the Representation of the People (Amendment) Act, 1992`
  line `(38 of 1992).]`
  line
  line `(2) Every assembly constituency referred to ^10[in sub-section (1) or sub-section (1A)] shall be a`
  line `single-member constituency.`
  line
  line `^11(3) The extent of each assembly constituency in all the States and Union Territories except the`
  line `assembly constituencies in the States of Arunachal Pradesh, Assam, Jharkhand, Manipur and`
  line `Nagaland shall be as determined by the orders of the Delimitation Commission made under the`
  line `provisions of the Delimitation Act, 2002 (33 of 2002) and the extent of each assembly constituency in`
  line `the States of Arunachal Pradesh, Assam, Jharkhand, Manipur and Nagaland shall be as provided for in`
  line `the Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies Order, 2008 having regard to the`
  line `provisions of sections 10A and 10B of the Delimitation Act, 2002 (33 of 2002).]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 4, for sections 7, 8 and 9 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 8 of 1980, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-9-1979).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 38 of 1992, s. 2, for "sub-sections (1A) and (1B)" (w.e.f. 5-12-1992).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 61 of 1968, s. 4, for "forty-six" (w.e.f. 31-12-1968).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "six seats" (w.e.f. 31-12-1968).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 8 of 1980, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-9-1979).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 40 of 1987, s. 2 (w.e.f. 22-9-1987).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 10 of 2008, s. 3, for "thirty-nine seats" (w.e.f. 16-4-2008).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 38 of 1992, s. 2 (w.e.f. 5-12-1992).`
  line
  line `10. Subs. by Act 8 of 1980, s. 2, for "in sub-section (1)" (w.e.f. 1-9-1979).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 10 of 2008, s. 3, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 16-4-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_a:
  sectionId (1101)
  sectionNo 7A
  orderNo 9
  title `Total number of seats in the Legislative Assembly of Sikkim and Assembly Constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content
  footnotes `1. . Ins. by Act 10 of 1976, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 9-9-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1101&sectionno=7A&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content:
  string
  line `^1 [7A. Total number of seats in the Legislative Assembly of Sikkim and Assembly Constituencies.--(1) Notwithstanding anything contained in section 7, in the Legislative Assembly`
  line `of the State of Sikkim [deemed under the Constitution (Thirty-sixth Amendment) Act, 1975 to be the Legislative Assembly of that State duly constituted], the total number of seats to be filled by persons`
  line `chosen by direct election from Assembly constituencies shall be 32.`
  line
  line `(2) Every Assembly constituency referred to in sub-section (1) shall be a single-member`
  line constituency.
  line
  line `(3) In the Legislative Assembly so deemed to be duly constituted, the extent of each constituency`
  line `and the reservation of seats shall be as provided for immediately before the commencement of the`
  line `Constitution (Thirty-sixth Amendment) Act, 1975.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (1102)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 10
  title `Consolidation of delimitation orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1102&sectionno=8&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Having regard to all the orders referred to in`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 4 and sub-section (3) of section 7 relating to the delimitation of`
  line `parliamentary and assembly constituencies in all States and Union Territories, except the States of`
  line `Arunachal Pradesh, Assam, Jharkhand, Manipur and Nagaland, made by the Delimitation`
  line `Commission and published in the Official Gazette, the Election Commission shall`
  line
  line `(a) after making such amendments as appear to it to be necessary for bringing up-to-date the`
  line `description of the extent of the parliamentary and assembly constituencies as given in such orders,`
  line `without, however, altering the extent of any such constituency;`
  line
  line `(b) after taking into account the provisions of the Delimitation of Parliamentary and`
  line `Assembly Constituencies Order, 1976, as made applicable pursuant to the orders made by the`
  line `President under section 10A of the Delimitation Act, 2002 (33 of 2002) relating to delimitation of`
  line `parliamentary and assembly constituencies in the States of Arunachal Pradesh, Assam, Manipur`
  line `and Nagaland, and the provisions of section 10B of the said Act relating to delimitation of`
  line `parliamentary and assembly constituencies in the State of Jharkhand,`
  line
  line `consolidate all such orders into one single order to be known as the Delimitation of Parliamentary and`
  line `Assembly Constituencies Order, 2008 and shall send authentic copies of that Order to the Central`
  line `Government and to the Government of each State having a Legislative Assembly; and thereupon that`
  line `Order shall supersede all the orders referred to in sub-section (5) of section 4 and sub-section (3) of`
  line `section 7 and shall have the force of law and shall not be called in question in any court.]`
  line
  line `(2) As soon as may be, after the said Order is received by the Central Government or by the`
  line `Government of a State, that Government shall cause it to be laid before the House of the People or,`
  line `as the case may be, the Legislative Assembly of the State.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) The consolidation under sub-section (1) of the orders referred to in sub-section (5) of`
  line `section 4, or as the case may be, sub-section (3) of section 7 shall not, ^3[as provided in sub-section (5) of section 10 of the Delimitation Act, 2002 (33 of 2002)], affect the representation in, and`
  line `the territorial constituencies of, the House of the People or the Legislative Assembly of the State`
  line `existing on the date of publication in the Gazette of India of any such order or orders as may be`
  line relevant.]
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2008, s. 4, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 16-4-2008).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 88 of 1976, s. 4.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 10 of 2008, s. 4, for certain words.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_a:
  sectionId (1103)
  sectionNo 8A
  orderNo 11
  title `Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly constituencies in the States of Arunachal Pardesh, Assam, Manipur or Nagaland.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 5, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1103&sectionno=8A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content:
  string
  line `^1-[8A. Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly Constituencies in the States of Arunachal`
  line `Pradesh, Assam, Manipur or Nagaland.(1) If the President is satisfied that the`
  line `situation and the conditions prevailing in the States of Arunachal Pradesh, Assam, Manipur or`
  line `Nagaland are conducive for the conduct of delimitation exercise, he may, by order, rescind the`
  line `deferment order issued under the provisions of section 10A of the Delimitation Act, 2002 (33 of 2002)`
  line `in relation to that State, and provide for the conduct of delimitation exercise in the State by the`
  line `Election Commission.`
  line
  line `(2) As soon as may be after the deferment order in respect of a State is rescinded under subsection`
  line `(1), the Election Commission may, by order, determine--`
  line
  line `(a) the parliamentary constituencies into which such State to which more than one seat is`
  line `allotted in the First Schedule shall be divided;`
  line
  line `(b) the extent of each constituency; and`
  line
  line `(c) the number of seats, if any, reserved for the Scheduled Castes or the Scheduled Tribes.`
  line
  line `(3) As soon as may be after the deferment order in respect of a State is rescinded under sub-section (1), the Election Commission may, by order, determine--`
  line
  line `(a) the assembly constituencies into which such State shall be divided for the purpose of`
  line `elections to the Legislative Assembly of that State;`
  line
  line `(b) the extent of each constituency; and`
  line
  line `(c) the number of seats, if any, reserved for the Scheduled Castes or the Scheduled Tribes.`
  line
  line `(4) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), the Election Commission shall, having regard to`
  line `the provisions of the Constitution and the principles specified in clauses (c) and (d) of sub-section (1)`
  line `of section 9 of the Delimitation Act, 2002 (33 of 2002) determine the parliamentary and assembly`
  line `constituencies in the States of Arunachal Pradesh, Assam, Manipur and Nagaland in which seats shall`
  line `be reserved, if any, for the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes.`
  line
  line `(5) The Election Commission shall,--`
  line
  line `(a) publish its proposals under sub-sections (2), (3) and (4) with respect to any State in the`
  line `Official Gazette and also in such other manner as it thinks fit;`
  line
  line `(b) specify a date on or after which the proposals will be further considered by it;`
  line
  line `(c) consider all objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before the`
  line `date so specified;`
  line
  line `(d) hold, for the purpose of such consideration, if it thinks fit so to do, one or more public`
  line `sittings at such place or places in such State as it thinks fit;`
  line
  line `(e) after considering all objections and suggestions which may have been received by it before`
  line `the date so specified, determine, by order, the delimitation of parliamentary and assembly`
  line `constituencies in the State and also the constituency or constituencies in which seats shall be`
  line `reserved, if any, for the Scheduled Castes and the Scheduled Tribes and cause such order to be`
  line `published in the Official Gazette; and, upon such publication, the order shall have the force of law`
  line `and shall not be called in question in any court and the Delimitation of Parliamentary and`
  line `Assembly Constituencies Order, 2008 shall be deemed to have been amended accordingly.`
  line
  line `(6) Every order made under sub-sections (1) and (2) and clause (e) of sub-section (5) shall be laid`
  line `before each House of Parliament.`
  line
  line `(7) Every order made under sub-sections (1) and (3) and clause (e) of sub-section (5) shall, as`
  line `soon as may be after it is published under that sub-section, be laid before the Legislative Assembly of`
  line `the State concerned.]`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (1104)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 12
  title `Power of Election Commission to maintain Delimitation Order up-to-date`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1104&sectionno=9&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Election Commission may, from time to time, by notification published in the Gazette of India and`
  line `in the Official Gazette of the State concerned,--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) correct any printing mistake in the Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly`
  line `Constituencies Order, 2008 or any error arising therein from inadvertent slip or omission;`
  line
  line `(aa) make such amendments in the Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly`
  line `Constituencies Order, 2008 as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for consolidating with that Order any notification or order relating to delimitation of Parliamentary or assembly`
  line `constituencies (including reservation of seats for the Scheduled Castes or the Scheduled Tribes in`
  line `such constituencies) issued under section 8A of this Act or any other Central Act;]`
  line
  line `(b) where the boundaries or name of any district or any territorial division mentioned in`
  line `the Order are or is altered, make such amendments as appear to it to be necessary or`
  line `expedient for bringing the Order up-to-date.`
  line
  line `^2[(c) make such amendments in the Delimitation of Parliamentary and Assembly`
  line `Constituencies Order, 2008 as appear to it to be necessary or expedient for bringing the Order upto-date`
  line `by including therein and excluding therefrom the relevant areas, consequent upon the`
  line `exchange of one hundred and eleven enclaves of India and fifty-one enclaves of Bangladesh with`
  line `effect from 31st July, 2015, in pursuance of the Constitution (One Hundredth Amendment) Act, 2015.]`
  line
  line `(2) Every notification under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is issued, before`
  line `the House of the People and the Legislative Assembly of the State concerned].`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 10 of 2008, s. 6, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 16-4-2008).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 10 of 2016, s. 2 (w.e.f. 4-3-2016).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_a:
  sectionId (1105)
  sectionNo 9A
  orderNo 13
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1105&sectionno=9A&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_content:
  string
  line `9A. [Power of Election Commission to determine the constituencies to be reserved for Scheduled`
  line `Tribes in main States.]Omitted by the Representation of the People (Amendment) Act, 2008 (10 of 2008), s. 7 (w.e.f. 16-4-2008).`
obj_root_law_sections_9_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9_b:
  sectionId (1106)
  sectionNo 9B
  orderNo 14
  title Omitted.
  content `9B.[Power Election Commission to determine certain.]Omitted by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 16-4-2008).`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1106&sectionno=9B&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_9_b_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (1107)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 15
  title `Allocation of seats in the Legislative Councils.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1107&sectionno=10&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) The allocation of seats in the`
  line `Legislative Councils of the States having such Councils shall be as shown in the Third Schedule.`
  line
  line `(2) In the Legislative Council of each State specified in the first column of the Third`
  line `Schedule, there shall be the number of seats specified in the second column thereof opposite to that`
  line `State, and of those seats,`
  line
  line `(a) the numbers specified in the third, fourth and fifth columns shall be the number of seats to`
  line `be filled by persons elected, respectively, by the electorates referred to in sub-clauses (a), (b)`
  line `and (c) of clause (3) of article 171;`
  line
  line `(b) the number specified in the sixth column shall be the number of seats to be filled by`
  line `persons elected by the members of the Legislative Assembly of the State from amongst`
  line `persons who are not members of that Assembly; and`
  line
  line `(c) the number specified in the seventh column shall be the number of seats to be filled by`
  line `persons nominated by the Governor ^1* * * of the State in accordance with the provisions of clause`
  line `(5) of article 171.`
  line
  line `^2* ****`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Omitted by the Act 10 of 2008, s. 7 (w.e.f. 16-4-2008).`
  line
  line `2. The words "or Rajpramukh, as the case may be" omitted by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956 (w.e.f. 1-11-`
  line `1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (1108)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 16
  title `Delimitation of Council constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1108&sectionno=11&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `As soon as may be after the commencement of`
  line `this Act, the President shall, by order, determine`
  line
  line `(a) the constituencies into which each State having a Legislative Council shall be divided`
  line `for the purpose of elections to that Council under each of the sub-clauses (a), (b) and (c) of`
  line `clause (3) of article 171;`
  line
  line `(b) the extent of each constituency; and`
  line
  line `(c) the number of seats allotted to each constituency.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (1109)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 17
  title `Power to alter or amend orders.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1109&sectionno=12&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] The President may, from time to time, after`
  line `consulting the Election Commission, by order, alter or amend any order made by him under ^2* * *section 11.`
  line
  line `^3[(2) An order under sub-section (1) may contain provisions for the allocation of any member representing any council constituency immediately before the making of the order to any constituency delimited a new or altered by the order and for such other incidental and`
  line `consequential matters as the President may deem necessary.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 12 renumbered as sub-section (1) of that section by Act 20 of 1960, s. 2 (w.e.f. 8-5-1960).`
  line
  line `2. The words and figures "section 6, section 9, or" omitted by Act 2 of 1956, s. 7..br`
  line `3. Ins. by Act 20 of 1960, s. 2 (w.e.f. 8-5-1960).`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (1110)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 18
  title `Procedure as to orders delimiting constituencies`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1110&sectionno=13&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `13. Procedure as to orders delimiting constituencies.--^1***`
  line
  line `(3) Every order made under ^2* * * section 11 or section 12 shall be laid before Parliament as soon as may be after it is made, and shall be subject to such modifications as Parliament may make on a motion made within twenty days from the date on which the order is so laid.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Sub-section (1) and (2) omitted by Act 2 of 1956, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-3-1956).`
  line
  line `2. The words and figures "section 6, section 9," omitted by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-3-1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_a:
  sectionId (1111)
  sectionNo 13A
  orderNo 19
  title `Chief electoral officers`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1111&sectionno=13A&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content:
  string
  line `^1,(1) There shall be for each State a chief electoral officer who`
  line `shall be such officer of Government as the Election Commission may, in consultation with that`
  line `Government, designate or nominate in this behalf.`
  line `(2) Subject to the superintendence, direction and control of the Election Commission, the`
  line `chief electoral officer shall supervise the preparation, revision and correction of all electoral rolls in`
  line `the State under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_aa:
  sectionId (1112)
  sectionNo 13AA
  orderNo 20
  title `District election officers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_aa_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_aa_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1112&sectionno=13AA&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_13_aa_content:
  string
  line `^1[13AA. District election officers.—(1) For each district in a State, ^2***, the Election`
  line `Commission shall, in consultation with the Government of the State, designate or nominate a district`
  line `election officer who shall be an officer of Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Election Commission may designate or nominate more than one such officer`
  line `for a district if the Election Commission is satisfied that the functions of the office cannot be`
  line `performed satisfactorily by one officer.`
  line
  line `(2) Where more than one district election officer are designated or nominated for a district`
  line `under the proviso to sub-section (1), the Election Commission shall in the order designating or`
  line `nominating the district election officers also specify the area in respect of which each such officer`
  line `shall exercise jurisdiction.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to the superintendence, direction and control of the chief electoral officer, the district`
  line `election officer shall coordinate and supervise all work in the district or in the area within his`
  line `jurisdiction in connection with the preparation and revision of the electoral rolls for all`
  line `parliamentary, assembly and council constituencies within the district.`
  line
  line `(4) The district election officer shall also perform such other functions as may be entrusted`
  line `to him by the Election Commission and the chief electoral officer.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_aa_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 5 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `2. The words "other than a Union territory," omitted by Act 2 of 2004, s. 2.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_b:
  sectionId (1113)
  sectionNo 13B
  orderNo 21
  title `Electoral registration officers`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1113&sectionno=13B&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_13_b_content:
  string
  line `(1) The electoral roll ^1[^2[for each parliamentary constituency in the State of Jammu and Kashmir or in a Union territory not having a Legislative`
  line `Assembly], each assembly constituency and each Council constituency] shall be prepared and`
  line `revised by an electoral registration officer who shall be such officer of Government or of a local`
  line `authority as the Election Commission may, in consultation with the Government of the State in`
  line `which the constituency is situated, designate or nominate in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) An electoral registration officer may, subject to any prescribed restrictions, employ such`
  line `persons as he thinks fit for the preparation and revision of the electoral roll for the constituency.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 103 of 1956, s. 65, for certain words.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 6, for certain words (w.e.f.14-12-1966).`
obj_root_law_sections_13_c:
  sectionId (1114)
  sectionNo 13C
  orderNo 22
  title `Assistant electoral registration officers`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_c_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_c_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1114&sectionno=13C&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_13_c_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Election Commission may appoint`
  line `one or more persons as assistant electoral registration officers to assist any electoral registration`
  line `officer in the performance of his functions.`
  line
  line `(2) Every assistant electoral registration officer shall, subject to the control of the electoral`
  line `registration officer, be competent to perform all or any of the functions of the electoral`
  line `registration officer.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_c_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13_cc:
  sectionId (1115)
  sectionNo 13CC
  orderNo 23
  title `Chief Electoral Officers, District Election Officers, etc., deemed to be on deputation to Election Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_cc_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 1 of 1989, s. 2 (w.e.f. 15-3-1989).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1115&sectionno=13CC&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_13_cc_content:
  string
  line `^1[13CC. Chief Electoral Officers, District Election Officers, etc., deemed to be on`
  line `deputation to Election Commission.—The officers referred to in this Part and any other officer`
  line `or staff employed in connection with the preparation, revision and correction of the electoral rolls`
  line `for, and the conduct of, all elections shall be deemed to be on deputation to the Election Commission`
  line `for the period during which they are so employed and such officers and staff shall, during that`
  line `period, be subject to the control, superintendence and discipline of the Election Commission.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13_d:
  sectionId (1116)
  sectionNo 13D
  orderNo 24
  title `Electoral rolls for Parliamentary constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_d_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 7, for section 13D (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1116&sectionno=13D&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_13_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[13D. Electoral rolls for parliamentary constituencies.—(1) The electoral roll for every`
  line `parliamentary constituency, other than a parliamentary constituency in the State of Jammu and`
  line `Kashmir or in a Union territory not having a Legislative Assembly, shall consist of the electoral`
  line `rolls for all the assembly constituencies comprised within that parliamentary constituency; and it`
  line `shall not be necessary to prepare or revise separately the electoral roll for any such parliamentary`
  line `constituency:`
  line
  line `Provided that for the period referred to in clause (2) of article 371A, it shall be necessary to`
  line `prepare and revise separately the electoral roll for that part of the parliamentary constituency of`
  line `Nagaland which comprises the Tuensang district and the provisions of Part III shall apply in`
  line `relation to the preparation and revision of the electoral roll of the said part as they apply in relation`
  line `to an assembly constituency.`
  line
  line `(2) The provisions of Part III shall apply in relation to every parliamentary constituency in`
  line `the State of Jammu and Kashmir or in a Union territory not having a Legislative Assembly as they`
  line `apply in relation to an assembly constituency.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (1117)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 25
  title Definitions
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1117&sectionno=14&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `^1[14. Definitions.--In this Part, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "constituency" means an Assembly constituency ^2*** ;`
  line
  line `(b) "qualifying date", in relation to the preparation or revision of every electoral roll under`
  line `this Part, means ^3[the 1st day of January, the 1st day of April, the 1st day of July and the 1st day`
  line `of October] of the year in which it is so prepared or revised:]`
  line
  line `^4[Provided that "qualifying date", in relation to the preparation or revision of every electoral`
  line `roll under this Part in the year 1989, shall be the 1st day of April, 1989.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 1956, s. 11, for section 14 (w.e.f. 1-3-1956).`
  line
  line `2. Certain words omitted by Act 103 of 1956, s. 65 (w.e.f. 1-1-1957).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 49 of 2021, s. 2, for "the 1st day of January" (w.e.f.1-8-2022).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 21 of 1989, s. 3 (w.e.f. 28-3-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (1118)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 26
  title `Electoral roll for every constituency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1118&sectionno=15&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `For every constituency there shall be an electoral`
  line `roll which shall be prepared in accordance with the provisions of this Act under the superintendence,`
  line `direction and control of the Election Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (1119)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 27
  title `Disqualifications for registration in an electoral roll.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1119&sectionno=16&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) A person shall be disqualified`
  line `for registration in an electoral roll if he`
  line
  line `(a) is not a citizen of India; or`
  line
  line `(b) is of unsound mind and stands so declared by a competent court; or`
  line
  line `(c) is for the time being disqualified from voting under the provisions of any law`
  line `relating to corrupt ^1* * * practices and other offences in connection with elections.`
  line
  line `(2) The name of any person who becomes so disqualified after registration shall forthwith be`
  line `struck off the electoral roll in which it is included:`
  line
  line `^2[Provided that the name of any person struck off the electoral roll of a constituency by reason of`
  line `a disqualification under clause (c) of sub-section (1) shall forthwith be re-instated in that roll if such`
  line `disqualification is, during the period such roll is in force, removed under any law authorising such`
  line removal.]
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. The words "and illegal" omitted by Act 58 of 1960, s. 3 and the Second Schedule (w.e.f. 26-12-1960).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 73 of 1950, s. 4 (w.e.f. 23-12-1950).`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (1120)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 28
  title `No person to be registered in more than one constituency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes `1. The words "in the same State" omitted by Act 58 of 1958, s. 6 (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1120&sectionno=17&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `No person shall be`
  line `entitled to be registered in the electoral roll for more than one constituency ^1`
  line `* * *.`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (1121)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 29
  title `No person to be registered more than once in any constituency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1121&sectionno=18&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `No person`
  line `shall be entitled to be registered in the electoral roll for any constituency more than once.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (1122)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 30
  title `Conditions of registration`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1122&sectionno=19&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `^1[19. Conditions of registration.Subject to the foregoing provisions of this Part, every`
  line `person who`
  line
  line `(a) is not less than ^2[eighteen years] of age on the qualifying date, and`
  line
  line `(b) is ordinarily resident in a constituency,`
  line
  line `shall be entitled to be registered in the electoral roll for that constituency.]`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 7, ibid., for section 19 (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 21 of 1989, s. 4, for "twenty-one years" (w.e.f. 28-3-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (1123)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 31
  title `Meaning of “ordinarily resident”`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1123&sectionno=20&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) A person shall not be deemed to be ordinarily`
  line `resident in a constituency on the ground only that he owns, or is in possession of, a dwelling house`
  line therein.
  line
  line `(1A) A person absenting himself temporarily from his place of ordinary residence shall not by`
  line `reason thereof cease to be ordinarily resident therein.`
  line
  line `(1B) A member of Parliament or of the Legislature of a State shall not during the term of his`
  line `office cease to be ordinarily resident in the constituency in the electoral roll of which he is registered`
  line `as an elector at the time of his election as such member, by reason of his absence from that`
  line `constituency in connection with his duties as such member.]`
  line
  line `(2) A person who is a patient in any establishment maintained wholly or mainly for the`
  line `reception and treatment of persons suffering from mental illness or mental defectiveness, or who is`
  line `detained in prison or other legal custody at any place, shall not by reason thereof be deemed to be`
  line `ordinarily resident therein.`
  line
  line `^2[(3) Any person having a service qualification shall be deemed to be ordinarily resident on any`
  line `date in the constituency in which, but for his having such service qualification, he would have been`
  line `ordinarily resident on that date.]`
  line
  line `(4) Any person holding any office in India declared^3`
  line `by the President in consultation with the`
  line `Election Commission to be an office to which the provisions of this sub-section apply,`
  line `^4*** shall be deemed to be ordinarily resident ^5*** on any date in the constituency in which, but for the holding of any such office ^6* * *, he would have been ordinarily resident ^7* * * on that date.`
  line
  line `(5) The statement of any such person as is referred to in sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) made in the prescribed form and verified in the prescribed manner, that ^8[but for his having the service qualification] or but for his holding any such office ^9* * * as is referred to in sub-section (4) he would have been ordinarily resident in a specified place ^10* * * on any date, shall, in the absence of evidence to the contrary, be ^8[accepted as correct].`
  line
  line `(6) The ^11[spouse] of any such person as is referred to in sub-section (3) or sub-section (4) shall ^12[if such spouse] be ordinarily residing with such person ^13* * * be deemed to be ordinarily resident on ^14*** in the constituency specified by such person under sub-section (5).`
  line
  line `^15[(7) If in any case a question arises as to where a person is ordinarily resident at any`
  line `relevant time, the question shall be determined with reference to all the facts of the case and to such rules as may be made in this behalf by the Central Government in consultation with the Election Commission.]`
  line
  line `(8) In sub-sections (3) and (5) service qualification means--`
  line
  line `(a) being a member of the armed forces of the Union; or`
  line
  line `(b) being a member of a force to which the provisions of the Army Act, 1950 (46 of 1950),`
  line `have been made applicable whether with or without modifications; or`
  line
  line `(c) being a member of an armed police force of a State, who is serving outside that State; or`
  line
  line `(d) being a person who is employed under the Government of India, in a post outside India.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 58 of 1958, s. 8, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 8, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `3. The following offices have been declared by the President by Notification No. S.O. 959, dated the 18th April, 1960:`
  line
  line `1. The President of India.`
  line
  line `2. The Vice-President of India.`
  line
  line `3. The Governors of States.`
  line
  line `4. Cabinet Ministers of the Union or of any State.`
  line
  line `5. The Deputy Chairman and Members of the Planning Commission.`
  line
  line `6. The Ministers of State of the Union or of any State.`
  line
  line `7. The Deputy Ministers of the Union or of any State.`
  line
  line `8. The Speaker of the House of the People or of any Legislative Assembly.`
  line
  line `9. The Chairman of any State Legislative Council.`
  line
  line `10. Lieutenant Governors of Union territories.`
  line
  line `11. The Deputy Speaker of the House of the People or of any State Legislative Assembly.`
  line
  line `12. The Deputy Chairman of the Council of States or of any State Legislative Council.`
  line
  line `13. The Parliamentary Secretaries of the Union or of any State.`
  line
  line `4. Certain words omitted by Act 47 of 1966, s. 8 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `5. The words during any period or omitted by Act 2 of 1956, s. 14.`
  line
  line `6. The words or employment omitted by Act 47 of 1966, s. 8 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `7. The words during any period or omitted by Act 2 of 1956, s. 14.`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 49 of 2021, s. 3, for "wife" (w.e.f. 1-8-2022).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "if she" (w.e.f. 1-8-2022).`
  line
  line `10. The words "during any period" omitted by Act 2 of 1956, s. 14 (w.e.f. 1-3-1956).`
  line
  line `11. The words "during that period" omitted by s. 14, ibid (w.e.f. 1-3-1956).`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 8 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `13. Ins. by Act 36 of 2010, s. 2 (w.e.f. 10-2-2011).`
  line `14. The words "during that period" omitted by s. 14, ibid (w.e.f. 1-3-1956).`
  line
  line `15. Ins. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 8 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
obj_root_law_sections_20_a:
  sectionId (1124)
  sectionNo 20A
  orderNo 32
  title `Special provisions for citizens of India residing outside India.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 36 of 2010, s. 2 (w.e.f. 10-2-2011).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1124&sectionno=20A&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_20_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[20A. Special provisions for citizens of India residing outside India.—(1) Notwithstanding`
  line `anything contained in this Act, every citizen of India`
  line
  line `(a) whose name in not included in the electoral roll;`
  line
  line `(b) who has not acquired the citizenship of any other country; and`
  line
  line `(c) who is absenting from his place of ordinary residence in India owing to his employment,`
  line `education or otherwise outside India (whether temporarily or not),`
  line
  line `shall be entitled to have his name registered in the electoral roll in the constituency in which his place`
  line `of residence in India as mentioned in his passport is located.`
  line
  line `(2) The time within which the name of persons referred to in sub-section (1) shall be registered in`
  line `the electoral roll and the manner and procedure for registering of a person in the electoral roll under`
  line `sub-section (1) shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every person registered under this section shall, if otherwise eligible to exercise his franchise,`
  line `be allowed to vote at an election in the constituency.]`
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (1125)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 33
  title `Preparation and revision of electoral rolls.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1125&sectionno=21&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `^1[21. Preparation and revision of electoral rolls.(1) The electoral roll for each constituency`
  line `shall be prepared in the prescribed manner by reference to the qualifying date and shall come into`
  line `force immediately upon its final publication in accordance with the rules made under this Act.`
  line
  line `^2[(2) The said electoral roll`
  line
  line `(a) shall, unless otherwise directed by the Election Commission for reasons to be recorded`
  line `in writing, be revised in the prescribed manner by reference to the qualifying date`
  line
  line `(i) before each general election to the House of the People or to the Legislative Assembly`
  line `of a State; and`
  line
  line `(ii) before each bye-election to fill a casual vacancy in a seat allotted to the`
  line `constituency; and`
  line
  line `(b) shall be revised in any year in the prescribed manner by reference to the qualifying date`
  line `if such revision has been directed by the Election Commission:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the electoral roll is not revised as aforesaid, the validity or continued operation of`
  line `the said electoral roll shall not thereby be affected.]`
  line
  line `(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), the Election Commission may`
  line `at any time, for reasons to be recorded, direct a special revision of the electoral roll for any`
  line `constituency or part of a constituency in such manner as it may think fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that subject to the other provisions of this Act, the electoral roll for the`
  line `constituency, as in force at the time of the issue of any such direction, shall continue to be in force until the completion of the special revision so directed.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 1956, s. 15, for sections 21 to 25.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 9, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (1126)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 34
  title `Correction of entries in electoral rolls.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1126&sectionno=22&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `^1[22. Correction of entries in electoral rolls.—If the electoral registration officer for a constituency, on application made to him or on his own motion, is satisfied after such inquiry as he thinks fit, that any entry in the electoral roll of the constituency—`
  line
  line `(a) is erroneous or defective in any particular,`
  line
  line `(b) should be transposed to another place in the roll on the ground that the person concerned`
  line `has changed his place of ordinary residence within the constituency, or`
  line
  line `(c) should be deleted on the ground that the person concerned is dead or has ceased to be`
  line `ordinarily resident in the constituency or is otherwise not entitled to be registered in that roll,`
  line
  line `the electoral registration officer shall, subject to such general or special directions, if any, as may be`
  line `given by the Election Commission in this behalf, amend, transpose or delete the entry ^2[after proper verification of facts in such manner as may be prescribed]:`
  line
  line `Provided that before taking any action on any ground under clause (a) or clause (b) or any`
  line `action under clause (c) on the ground that the person concerned has ceased to be ordinarily resident in the constituency or that he is otherwise not entitled to be registered in the electoral roll of`
  line `that constituency, the electoral registration officer shall give the person concerned a reasonable`
  line `opportunity of being heard in respect of the action proposed to be taken in relation to him ^3[after`
  line `proper verification of facts in such manner as may be prescribed].`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 58 of 1958, s. 9, for section 22.`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 36 of 2010, s. 3 (w.e.f. 10-2-2011).`
  line
  line `3 Ins. by Act 36 of 2010, s. 3 (w.e.f. 10-2-2011).`
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (1127)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 35
  title `Inclusion of names in electoral rolls.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1127&sectionno=23&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `^1[23. Inclusion of names in electoral rolls.-(1) Any person whose name is not included in the`
  line `electoral roll of a constituency may apply to the electoral registration officer for the inclusion of his`
  line `name in that roll.`
  line
  line `(2) The electoral registration officer shall, if satisfied that the applicant is entitled to be registered`
  line `in the electoral roll, direct his name to be included therein ^2[after proper verification of facts in such`
  line `manner as may be prescribed]:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the applicant is registered in the electoral roll of any other constituency, the`
  line `electoral registration officer shall inform the electoral registration officer of that other constituency`
  line `and that officer shall, on receipt of the information, strike off the applicant's name from that roll ^2[after proper verification of facts in such manner as may be prescribed].`
  line
  line `(3) No amendment, transposition or deletion of any entry shall be made under section 22 and no`
  line `direction for the inclusion of a name in the electoral roll of a constituency shall be given under this`
  line `section, after the last date for making nominations for an election in that constituency or in the`
  line `parliamentary constituency within which that constituency is comprised and before the completion of`
  line `that election.]`
  line
  line `^3[(4) The electoral registration officer may for the purpose of establishing the identity of any`
  line `person require that such person may furnish the Aadhaar number given by the Unique Identification`
  line `Authority of India as per the provisions of the Aadhaar (Targeted Delivery of Financial and Other`
  line `Subsidies, Benefits and Services) Act, 2016 (18 of 2016):`
  line
  line `Provided that the electoral registration officer may also require the Aadhaar number from persons`
  line `already included in the electoral roll for the purposes of authentication of entries in electoral roll and`
  line `to identify registration of name of the same person in the electoral roll of more than one constituency`
  line `or more than once in the same constituency.`
  line
  line `(5) Every person whose name is included in the electoral roll may intimate his Aadhaar number to`
  line `such authority in such form and manner as may be prescribed, on or before a *date to be notified by the`
  line `Central Government in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(6) No application for inclusion of name in the electoral roll shall be denied and no entries in the`
  line `electoral roll shall be deleted for inability of an individual to furnish or intimate Aadhaar number due`
  line `to such sufficient cause as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that such individual may be allowed to furnish such other alternate documents as may be`
  line prescribed.
  line
  line `Explanation.-For the purposes of this section, the expression Aadhaar number shall have the`
  line `same meaning as assigned to it in clause (a) of Section 2 of the Aadhaar (Targeted Delivery of`
  line `Financial and Other Subsidies, Benefits and Services) Act, 2016 (18 of 2016).]`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 10, for s. 23 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 36 of 2010, s. 4 (w.e.f. 10-2-2011)`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 49 of 2021, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-8-2022).`
  line
  line `*1st April, 20233 section 25 (5), vide notification No. S.O. 2805(E), dated 17th June, 2022, see Gazette of India,`
  line `Extraordinary, Part II, sec. 3 (ii)`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (1128)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 36
  title Appeals.
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1128&sectionno=24&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `^1[24. Appeals.An appeal shall lie within such time and in such manner as may be prescribed`
  line
  line `(a) to the ^2[district magistrate or additional district magistrate or executive magistrate or`
  line `district collector or an officer of equivalent rank], from any order of the electoral registration`
  line `officer under section 22 or section 23 ^3***.`
  line
  line `^4[(b) to the chief electoral officer, from any order of the district magistrate or the additional`
  line `district magistrate under clause (a)]`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1961, s. 3 (w.e.f. 20-9-1961).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 41 of 2009, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-2-2010).`
  line
  line `3. The word "and" omitted by Act 47 of 1966, s. 11 (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 41 of 2009, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-2-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (1129)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 37
  title `Fee for applications and appeals`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1129&sectionno=25&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `Every applications under section 22 or section 23 and`
  line `every appeal under section 24 shall be accompanied by the prescribed fee which shall, in no case,`
  line `be refunded.]`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25_a:
  sectionId (1130)
  sectionNo 25A
  orderNo 38
  title `Conditions of registration as elector in Sangha constituency in Sikkim.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 10 of 1976, s. 2 and the Schedule. (w.e.f. 9-9-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1130&sectionno=25A&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_25_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[25A. Conditions of registration as elector in Sangha constituency in Sikkim.—Notwithstanding anything contained in sections 15 and 19, for the Sangha constituency in the State`
  line `of Sikkim, only the Sanghas belonging to monasteries, recognised for the purpose of the elections`
  line `held in Sikkim in April, 1974, for forming the Assembly for Sikkim, shall be entitled to be`
  line `registered in the electoral roll, and the said electoral roll shall, subject to the provisions of sections 21`
  line `to 25, be prepared or revised in such manner as may be directed by the Election Commission, in`
  line `consultation with the Government of Sikkim.]`
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (1131)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 39
  title Omitted.
  content `^1 26. [Preparation of electoral rolls for Assembly constituencies.] Omitted by the Representation of the People (Amendment) Act, 1956 (2 of1956), s. 17.`
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 1956, s. 16, for the heading.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1131&sectionno=26&orderno=39&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (1132)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 40
  title `Preparation of electoral rolls for Council Constituencies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1132&sectionno=27&orderno=40&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) In this section, "local`
  line `authorities' constituency", "graduates' constituency" and "teachers' constituency" mean a constituency`
  line `for the purpose of elections to a Legislative Council under sub-clause (a), sub-clause (b) and`
  line `sub-clause (c), respectively, of clause (3) of article 171.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) For the purpose of elections to the Legislative Council of a State in any local authorities'`
  line constituency--
  line
  line `(a) the electorate shall consist of members of such local authorities exercising jurisdiction in`
  line `any place or area within the limits of that constituency as are specified in relation to that State in`
  line `the Fourth Schedule;`
  line
  line `(b) every member of each such local authority within a local authorities' constituency`
  line `shall be entitled to be registered in the electoral roll for that constituency;`
  line
  line `(c) the electoral registration officer for every local authorities' constituency shall maintain`
  line `in his office in the prescribed manner and form the electoral roll for that constituency`
  line `corrected up-to-date;`
  line
  line `(d) in order to enable the electoral registration officer to maintain the electoral roll corrected`
  line `up-to-date, the chief executive officer of every local authority (by whatever designation such`
  line `officer may be known) shall immediately inform the electoral registration officer about every`
  line `change in the membership of that local authority; and the electoral registration officer shall, on`
  line `receipt of the information, strike off from the electoral roll the names of persons who have`
  line `ceased to be, and include therein the names of persons who have become, members of that`
  line `local authority; and`
  line
  line `(e) the provisions of sections 15, 16, 18, 22 and 23 shall apply in relation to local`
  line `authorities' constituencies as they apply in relation to assembly constituencies.]`
  line
  line `(3) For the purpose of elections to the Legislative Council of a State in the graduates'`
  line `constituencies and the teachers' constituencies, the State Government concerned may, with the`
  line `concurrence of the Election Commission, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify--`
  line
  line `(a) the qualifications which shall be deemed to be equivalent to that of a graduate of a`
  line `university in the territory of India, and`
  line
  line `(b) the educational institutions within the State not lower in standard than that of a`
  line `secondary school.`
  line
  line `^2[(4) The provisions of sections 15, 16, 18, 21, 22 and 23 shall apply in relation to graduates'`
  line `constituencies and teachers' constituencies as they apply in relation to assembly constituencies.]`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to the foregoing provisions of this section,--`
  line
  line `^3* * * * *`
  line
  line `^4[(a)] every person who ^5[is] ordinarily resident in a graduates' constituency and has, for at`
  line `least three years ^6[before the qualifying date], been either a graduate of a University in the`
  line `territory of India or in possession of any of the qualifications specified under`
  line `clause (a) of sub-section (3) by the State Government concerned, shall be entitled to be`
  line `registered in the electoral roll for that constituency; and`
  line
  line `^7[(b)] every person who ^5[is] ordinarily resident in a teachers' constituency, and has,`
  line `within the six years immediately ^6[before the qualifying date] for a total period of at least three`
  line `years, been engaged in teaching in any of the educational institutions specified under clause (b)`
  line `of sub-section (3) by the State Government concerned shall be entitled to be registered in the`
  line `electoral roll for that constituency.`
  line
  line `^8[(6) For the purposes of sub-sections (4) and (5) the qualifying date shall be the 1st day of`
  line `November of the year in which the preparation or revision of the electoral roll is commenced.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by s. 18, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-3-1956).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 2 of 1956, s. 18(b), for sub-section (4) (w.e.f. 1-3-1956).`
  line
  line `3. Clause (a) omitted by s. 18(c), ibid. (w.e.f. 1-3-1956).`
  line
  line `4. Clause (b) re-lettered as clause (a) by s. 18(c), ibid. (w.e.f. 1-3-1956).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 40 of 1961, s. 4, for "on the qualifying date was" (w.e.f. 20-9-1961).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for "before that date" (w.e.f. 20-9-1961).`
  line
  line `7. Clause (c) re-lettered as clause (b) by Act 2 of 1956, s. 18(c) (w.e.f. 1-3-1956).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 40 of 1961, s. 4(b), ibid., for sub-section (6) (w.e.f. 20-9-1961). Earlier sub-section (6) was substituted by`
  line `Act 2 of 1956, s. 18(d) (w.e.f. 1-3-1956).`
obj_root_law_sections_27_a:
  sectionId (1133)
  sectionNo 27A
  orderNo 41
  title `Constitution of electoral colleges for the filling of seats in the Council of States allotted to Union territories.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1133&sectionno=27A&orderno=41&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_27_a_content:
  string
  line `^1,^2,(1) ^3For the purpose of filling any seat or seats in the Council of States`
  line `allotted to any ^4Union territory ^5* * * in the Fourth Schedule to the Constitution there shall be an`
  line `electoral college for ^4each such territory ^6* * *.`
  line
  line ^7*****
  line
  line ^8*****
  line
  line `^9,^10(3) The electoral college for the Union territory of Delhi shall consist of the elected members of`
  line `the Legislative Assembly constituted for that territory under the Government of National Capital`
  line `Territory of Delhi Act, 1991 (1 of 1992).`
  line
  line `^11(4) ^12The electoral college for the Union territory of ^13*** Pondicherry shall consist of the elected`
  line `members of the Legislative Assembly constituted for that territory under the Government of Union`
  line `Territories Act, 1963 (20 of 1963).`
  line
  line ^14*****
  line ^15*****
  line `STATE AMENDMENTS`
  line
  line `Jammu and Kashmir and Ladakh (UTs).--`
  line
  line `Section 27A.-- After sub-section (4), insert the following sub-section, namely:-`
  line
  line `(5) The electoral college of the Union territory of Jammu and Kashmir shall consist of the elected`
  line `members of the Legislative Assembly constituted for that territory under the Jammu and Kashmir`
  line `Reorganization Act, 2019 (34 of 2019).`
  line
  line `[Vide the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020,`
  line `notification No. S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020).]`
obj_root_law_sections_27_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 73 of 1950, s. 8 (w.e.f. 23-12-1950).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order, 1956, for Part C States.`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 29 of 1975, s. 11, for certain words (w.e.f. 15-8-1975).`
  line
  line `4. The words "or group of such States" omitted by the Adaptation of Laws (No. 2) Order , 1956.`
  line
  line `5. Subs., ibid., for "each such State".`
  line
  line `6. The words "or group of States" omitted by Act 2 of 1956. s. 19.`
  line
  line `7. The proviso omitted by s.19, ibid.`
  line
  line `8. Omitted by Act 20 of 1963, s. 57(1)(b) and the Second Schedule. Earlier sub-section (2) was amended by Act 49 of`
  line `1951, s.44 and Schudle 5 (w.e.f. 13-5-1963).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 103 of 1956, s. 65, for sub-sections (3), (4) or (5) (w.e.f. 1-1-1957).`
