obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (1144)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 52
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1144&sectionno=28&orderno=52&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, after consulting the`
  line `Election Commission, by notification in the Official Gazette, make rules for carrying out the`
  line `purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules`
  line `may provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:`
  line
  line `^1[(a) the determination of ordinary residence under sub-section (7) of section 20;`
  line
  line `(aa) the particulars to be entered in the electoral rolls;]`
  line
  line `(b) the preliminary publication of electoral rolls ^2* * *;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner in which and the time within which claims and objections as to entries in`
  line `electoral rolls may be preferred;`
  line
  line ^3*****
  line
  line `(e) the manner in which notices of claims or objections shall be published;`
  line
  line `(f) the place, date and time at which claims or objections shall be heard and the manner in`
  line `which claims or objections shall be heard and disposed of;`
  line
  line `(g) the final publication of electoral rolls;`
  line
  line `^4[(h) the revision and correction of electoral roll and inclusion of names therein;]`
  line
  line `^5[(hh) the procedure for proper verification of facts for amending, transposing or deleting any entry in the electoral rolls, under section 22;`
  line
  line `(hhh) the procedure for proper verification of facts for inclusion of or striking off, names in`
  line `the electoral rolls, under sub-section (2) of section 23;]`
  line
  line `^6[(hhha) the authority and the form and manner of intimation of Aadhaar number under`
  line `sub-section (5) of section 23;`
  line
  line `(hhhb) the sufficient cause and furnishing of alternate documents to be provided by the`
  line `individual under sub-section (6) of section 23;]`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter required to be prescribed by this Act.`
  line
  line `^7[(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may`
  line `be after it is made, before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty`
  line `days which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before`
  line `the expiry of the session immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid,`
  line `both Houses agree in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should`
  line `not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the`
  line `case may be; so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to be`
  line `validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 47 of 1966, s. 12, for clause (a) (w.e.f. 14-12-1966).`
  line
  line `2. Certain words omitted by Act 73 of 1950, s. 9.`
  line
  line `3. Omitted by Act 20 of 1960, s. 3.`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 2 of 1956, s. 24, for clause (h).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 36 of 2010, s. 5 (w.e.f. 10-2-2011).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 49 of 2021, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-8-2022)`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 88 of 1976, s. 6, for sub-section (3).`
obj_root_law_sections_29:
  sectionId (1145)
  sectionNo (29)
  orderNo 53
  title `Staff of local authorities to be made available.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_29_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 2 of 1956, s. 25, for section 29.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1145&sectionno=29&orderno=53&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_29_content:
  string
  line `^1[29. Staff of local authorities to be made available.—Every local authority in a State shall,`
  line `when so requested by the chief electoral officer of the State, make available to any electoral`
  line `registration officer such staff as may be necessary for the performance of any duties in connection`
  line `with the preparation and revision of electoral rolls.]`
obj_root_law_sections_30:
  sectionId (1146)
  sectionNo (30)
  orderNo 54
  title `Jurisdiction of civil courts barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_30_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1146&sectionno=30&orderno=54&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_30_content:
  string
  line `No civil court shall have jurisdiction—`
  line
  line `(a) to entertain or adjudicate upon any question whether any person is or is not entitled to`
  line `be registered in an electoral roll for a constituency; or`
  line
  line `(b) to question the legality of any action taken by or under the authority of an electoral`
  line `registration officer, or of any decision given by any authority appointed under this Act for the`
  line `revision of any such roll.`
obj_root_law_sections_30_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_31:
  sectionId (1147)
  sectionNo (31)
  orderNo 55
  title `Making false declarations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_31_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1147&sectionno=31&orderno=55&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_31_content:
  string
  line `^1[^2[31. Making false declarations.If any person makes in connection with—`
  line
  line `(a) the preparation, revision or correction of an electoral roll, or`
  line
  line `(b) the inclusion or exclusion of any entry in or from an electoral roll,`
  line
  line `a statement or declaration in writing which is false and which he either knows or believes to be`
  line `false or does not believe to be true, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may`
  line `extend to one year, or with fine, or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_31_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 58 of 1958, s. 11.`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 20 of 1960, s. 4, for section 31.`
obj_root_law_sections_32:
  sectionId (1148)
  sectionNo (32)
  orderNo 56
  title `Breach of official duty in connection with the preparation, etc., of electoral rolls`
  content obj_root_law_sections_32_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 21 of 1996, s. 2, for certain words (w.e.f. 1-8-1996).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506&sectionId=1148&sectionno=32&orderno=56&orgactid=AC_CEN_3_20_00016_195043_1517807321506
obj_root_law_sections_32_content:
  string
  line `(1) If`
  line `any electoral registration officer, assistant electoral registration officer or other person required by`
  line `or under this Act to perform any official duty in connection with the preparation, revision or`
  line `correction of an electoral roll or the inclusion or exclusion of any entry in or from that roll, is`
  line `without reasonable cause, guilty of any act or omission in breach of such official duty, he shall be`
  line `punishable ^1[with imprisonment for a term which shall not be less than three months but which may`
  line `extend to two years and with fine].`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against any such officer or other person for`
  line `damages in respect of any such act or omission as aforesaid.`
  line
  line `(3) No court shall take cognizance of any offence punishable under sub-section (1) unless there`
  line `is a complaint made by order of, or under authority from, the Election Commission or the Chief`
  line `Electoral Officer of the State concerned.]`
